{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73178222.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73178222"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 51, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51"}}, "title": "added logic to statically link FFTW to use conda numpy with MKL."}, "content": {"raw": "Is there an easy way to test for general \u201cfalse\u201d values of the flag?  For instance, I think this will still do the static linking if FFTW\\_STATIC=0.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Is there an easy way to test for general \u201cfalse\u201d values of the flag?  For instance, I think this will still do the static linking if FFTW_STATIC=0.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-16T14:58:54.157410+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Keaton Burns", "uuid": "{3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e31a7835-5317-4dfa-8551-f32a06f40279/40f33f99-2b75-4a17-a8c2-07c8d74c7480/128"}}, "nickname": "kburns", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e31a7835-5317-4dfa-8551-f32a06f40279"}, "updated_on": "2018-08-16T14:58:54.165262+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 73178222}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73183795.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73183795"}}, "parent": {"id": 73178222, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73178222.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73178222"}}, "depth": 1}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 51, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51"}}, "title": "added logic to statically link FFTW to use conda numpy with MKL."}, "content": {"raw": "The problem is I don\u2019t know of an environment variable standard to be \u201cfalse\u201d. Should it be zero? FALSE? false? I tried googling around with little success. So, instead, I chose to make it a flag. Existence itself means true, nonexistence is false.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The problem is I don\u2019t know of an environment variable standard to be \u201cfalse\u201d. Should it be zero? FALSE? false? I tried googling around with little success. So, instead, I chose to make it a flag. Existence itself means true, nonexistence is false.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-16T15:35:54.491629+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "J. S. Oishi", "uuid": "{ab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:94f96ca9-adbd-4972-8f41-b00b9683f819/4a90742a-28a5-4829-a074-c23c9f5fcc81/128"}}, "nickname": "jsoishi", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:94f96ca9-adbd-4972-8f41-b00b9683f819"}, "updated_on": "2018-08-16T15:35:54.499356+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 73183795}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73186748.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73186748"}}, "parent": {"id": 73183795, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73183795.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73183795"}}, "depth": 2}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 51, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51"}}, "title": "added logic to statically link FFTW to use conda numpy with MKL."}, "content": {"raw": "I think a decent stdlib function to handle it is [distutils.util.strtobool](https://docs.python.org/3/distutils/apiref.html#distutils.util.strtobool), which will look for all of those kinds of things.  But it returns an integer 1/0 which then needs to be casted to a bool.  It might also be useful to throw in a print statement showing the determined value of \u201cfftw\\_static\u201d to help debug installation procedures.  Happy to add these in later if you don't want to bother now.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think a decent stdlib function to handle it is <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/distutils/apiref.html#distutils.util.strtobool\" rel=\"nofollow\">distutils.util.strtobool</a>, which will look for all of those kinds of things.  But it returns an integer 1/0 which then needs to be casted to a bool.  It might also be useful to throw in a print statement showing the determined value of \u201cfftw_static\u201d to help debug installation procedures.  Happy to add these in later if you don't want to bother now.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-16T15:56:57.503597+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Keaton Burns", "uuid": "{3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d3e64f1-bf12-45df-b655-4543d8fb34c4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e31a7835-5317-4dfa-8551-f32a06f40279/40f33f99-2b75-4a17-a8c2-07c8d74c7480/128"}}, "nickname": "kburns", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e31a7835-5317-4dfa-8551-f32a06f40279"}, "updated_on": "2018-08-16T15:56:57.511717+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 73186748}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73188433.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73188433"}}, "parent": {"id": 73186748, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51/comments/73186748.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51/_/diff#comment-73186748"}}, "depth": 3}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 51, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/51.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/dedalus-project/dedalus/pull-requests/51"}}, "title": "added logic to statically link FFTW to use conda numpy with MKL."}, "content": {"raw": "I already added the print statement; I'll add the `strtobool` when I get\nback from lunch.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I already added the print statement; I'll add the <code>strtobool</code> when I get\nback from lunch.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-16T16:10:15.500696+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "J. S. Oishi", "uuid": "{ab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bab7c2db2-7642-47a8-9264-0939f601d904%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:94f96ca9-adbd-4972-8f41-b00b9683f819/4a90742a-28a5-4829-a074-c23c9f5fcc81/128"}}, "nickname": "jsoishi", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:94f96ca9-adbd-4972-8f41-b00b9683f819"}, "updated_on": "2018-08-16T16:10:15.540701+00:00"